w23b42pdn2.name: Ahmad Ibrahim Mosque
w23b42pdn2.remarks: Built in 1958, this old generation zinc-roofed mosque located in the North part of the island serves the religious needs of Muslim living and working in the vicinity. It can accommodate 200 Muslims at any one time. It offers nursery, kindergarten and weekend madrasah classes for children of nearby residents. Altogether, a total of 480 children attend classes at various times, at the masjid. Since the â€˜70s, there have been several renovation and repair works carried out.
